Titulo: Enhancing the steam electrolysis by simultaneously regulating the electron and oxygen ion conductivity of la1-xsr1+xfeo4-δ oxides

Sentencas: oxides with different Sr content are investigated as air electrodes for solid oxide electrolytic cells.
Titulo: Enhancing the steam electrolysis by simultaneously regulating the electron and oxygen ion conductivity of la1-xsr1+xfeo4-δ oxides

Sentencas: The increased Sr content in La1-xSr1+xFeO4-delta significantly improves the electronic and oxygen ionic conductivity, enhancing the oxygen evolution reaction (OER) activity and electrochemical performance of steam electrolysis.
Titulo: Enhancing the steam electrolysis by simultaneously regulating the electron and oxygen ion conductivity of la1-xsr1+xfeo4-δ oxides

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of the La0.8Sr1.2FeO4-delta symmetrical cell reaches 1.04 Omega cm2 at 800 degrees C, and the electrolysis cell delivers a current density of -1709 mA cm-2 at 1.3 V, corresponding to the hydrogen production rates of 714 ml/(cm2 h).
Titulo: Enhancing the steam electrolysis by simultaneously regulating the electron and oxygen ion conductivity of la1-xsr1+xfeo4-δ oxides

Sentencas: Moreover, adding Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-delta (SDC) oxide further improves the steam electrolysis performance due to enhanced three-phase boundary active sites.
Titulo: Enhancing the steam electrolysis by simultaneously regulating the electron and oxygen ion conductivity of la1-xsr1+xfeo4-δ oxides

Sentencas: The electrolysis cell with La0.8Sr1.2FeO4-delta-SDC electrode exhibits excellent stability for over 200 h and cycling durability for 100 h under 750 degrees C and 1.2 V in 50%H2O-H2 condition.
Titulo: Enhancing the steam electrolysis by simultaneously regulating the electron and oxygen ion conductivity of la1-xsr1+xfeo4-δ oxides
